 Scaling up of this capacity goes very slow because, on the one hand, the
 creation of a new raw material flow takes years, but on the other hand,
 because many earth metals are byproducts when another raw material is mined.
 Therefore, an increase in need of the byproduct might not be feasible if
 there is no similar increase in the other raw material.
\end_layout

